statement.p:
Solve each system using augmented matrix notation. Express the solution using vectors (that is, in a set-builder notation using vectors and real-variable parameters).




						\syseq{
						3x  +  6y  =  18 ; 
                   					x  +  2y  =  6  
						}





							\syseq{
							x  +  y   =  1; 
                   						x  -  y   =  -1  
							}





							\syseq{
							x_1  \+ \. +  x_3   =  4; 
                   						x_1  -  x_2  +  2x_3  =  5; 
                  						4x_1  -  x_2  +  5x_3  =  17  
							}





							\syseq{
							2a   +  b    -  c     =  2;
							2a   \+ \. +  c   =  3;
                    						a   -  b  \+ \. =  0   
							}





							\syseq{
							  x  +  2y   -   z \+ \. =  3; 
                    						2x  +  y \+ \.   w   =  4; 
                     						x  -  y    +   z   +   w   =  1  
							}





							\syseq{
							x  \+ \. +  z   +   w   =  4;
                    						2x  +  y  \+ \. -   w   =  2;
                    						3x  +  y    +   z   \+ \. =  7  
							}

ol.li:
This reduction


								\amat{
								3 6 18;
								1 2 6
								}
								\quad\xrightarrow{}\quad
								&\amat{
								3 6 18;
								0 0 0
								}


						leaves x leading and y free. Making y the parameter, gives x=6-2y and this solution set:
						\bigl\{\vec{6 0} + \vec{-2 1}y \mid y \text{ in }\R\bigr\}

A reduction


								\amat{
								1  1  1 ;
              							1  -1 -1
								}
								\quad\xrightarrow{}\quad
								&\amat{
								1  1  1 ;
              							0  -2 -2
								}


						gives the unique solution y=1, x=0. The solution set is:
						\bigl\{\vec{0 1}\bigr\}

Row reduction gives


								\amat{
								 1  0  1  4; 
              							1  -1 2  5; 
              							4  -1 5  17
								}
								\quad\xrightarrow{}\quad
								&\amat{
								1  0  1  4; 
              							0  -1 1  1;  
              							0  -1 1  1
								}


								\quad\xrightarrow{}\quad
								&\amat{
								1  0  1  4; 
              							0  -1 1  1;  
             							0  0  0  0
								}


						leaves x_1 and x_2 pivot variables and x_3 a free variable. The solution set is:
						\bigl\{\vec{4 -1 0} + \vec{-1 1 1}x_3 \mid x_3 \text{ in }\R\bigr\}

This reduction


								\amat{
								2  1  -1 2; 
              							2  0  1  3; 
              							1  -1 0  0
								}
								\quad\xrightarrow{}\quad
								&\amat{
								2  1   -1   2 ;
              							0  -1   2    1;
              							0  -3/2 1/2  -1
								}


								\quad\xrightarrow{}\quad
								\amat{
								2  1  -1   2;
              							0  -1  2    1;  
              							0  0  -5/2 -5/2
								}


						shows that the solution set is a singleton set
							\bigl\{\vec{1 1 1}\bigr\}

Row reducing, we obtain


								\amat{
								1  2  -1 0  3;
              							2  1  0  1  4;
              							1  -1 1  1  1
								}
								\quad\xrightarrow{}\quad
								&\amat{
								1  2  -1 0  3;
              							0  -3 2  1  -2;
              							0  -3 2  1  -2
								}


								\quad\xrightarrow{}\quad
								&\amat{
								 1  2  -1 0  3;
             							 0  -3 2  1  -2;
              							0  0  0  0  0
								}


						and we end up with x and y pivotal variables while z and w are free. Solving for y gives y=(2+2z+w)/3 and substiting shows that x+2(2+2z+w)/3-z=3 so x=(5/3)-(1/3)z-(2/3)w, making this the solution set:
						\bigl\{\vec{\frac{5}{3} \frac{2}{3} 0 0} + \vec{-\frac{1}{3} \frac{2}{3} 1 0} z  + \vec{-\frac{2}{3} \frac{1}{3} 0 1}w \mid z, w  \text{ in }  \R \bigr\}

The reduction


								\amat{
								1  0  1  1  4; 
              							2  1  0  -1 2;
              							3  1  1  0  7
								}
								\quad\xrightarrow{}\quad
								&\amat{
								1  0  1  1  4;
              							0  1  -2 -3 -6;
              							0  1  -2 -3 -5
								}


								\quad\xrightarrow{}\quad
								&\amat{
								1  0  1  1  4;
              							0  1  -2 -3 -6;
              							0  0  0  0  1
								}


						shows that there is no solution, i.e., the solution set is empty.

statement.p:
Solve each system using matrix notation. Describe each solution using vectors, as in the preceeding problem.




							\syseq{
							2x  +  y  -  z  =  1; 
                  						4x  -  y  \+ \. =  3  
							}





							\syseq{
							x  \+ \. -  z  \+ \. =  1;
                     						\. \+  y  +  2z -  w  =  3;
                   						x  +  2y +  3z -  w  =  7  
							}





							\syseq{
							x  -  y  +  z \+ \. =  0;
                      						\. \+ y  \+ \. +  w  =  0;
                  						3x  -  2y +  3z +  w  =  0;
                      						\. - y \+ \. -  w  =  0  
							}





							\syseq{
							 a  +  2b +  3c +  d  -  e  =  1;
                  						3a  -  b  +  c  +  d  +  e  =  3  
							}
